#: ../../../contributing.rst:25
msgid "How to Suggest Improvements"
msgstr "如何提出改善建議"

#: ../../../contributing.rst:27
msgid ""
"To suggest an improvement, please create a Vyper Improvement Proposal (VIP "
"for short) using the `VIP Template <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/blob/"
"master/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/vip.md>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:31
msgid "How to Report Issues"
msgstr "如何回報議題"

#: ../../../contributing.rst:33
msgid ""
"To report an issue, please use the `GitHub issues tracker <https://github."
"com/vyperlang/vyper/issues>`_. When reporting issues, please mention the "
"following details:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:37
msgid "Which version of Vyper you are using"
msgstr "您使用的是哪個版本的 Vyper"

#: ../../../contributing.rst:38
msgid "What was the source code (if applicable)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:39
msgid "Which platform are you running on"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:40
msgid "Your operating system name and version"
msgstr "您的作業系統名稱和版本"

#: ../../../contributing.rst:41
msgid "Detailed steps to reproduce the issue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:42
msgid "What was the result of the issue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:43
msgid "What the expected behaviour is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:45
msgid ""
"Reducing the source code that caused the issue to a bare minimum is always "
"very helpful and sometimes even clarifies a misunderstanding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:49
msgid "Fix Bugs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:51
msgid ""
"Find or report bugs at our `issues page <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/"
"issues>`_. Anything tagged with \"bug\" is open to whoever wants to "
"implement it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:54
msgid "Style Guide"
msgstr "風格指南"

#: ../../../contributing.rst:56
msgid ""
"Our :ref:`style guide<style-guide>` outlines best practices for the Vyper "
"repository. Please ask us on the `Vyper (Smart Contract Programming "
"Language) Discord <https://discord.gg/6tw7PTM7C2>`_ ``#compiler-dev`` "
"channel if you have questions about anything that is not outlined in the "
"style guide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:59
msgid "Workflow for Pull Requests"
msgstr "拉取請求的工作流程"

#: ../../../contributing.rst:61
msgid ""
"In order to contribute, please fork off of the ``master`` branch and make "
"your changes there. Your commit messages should detail *why* you made your "
"change in addition to *what* you did (unless it is a tiny change)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:65
msgid ""
"If you need to pull in any changes from ``master`` after making your fork "
"(for example, to resolve potential merge conflicts), please avoid using "
"``git merge`` and instead, ``git rebase`` your branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:70
msgid "Commit Messages"
msgstr "送交訊息"

#: ../../../contributing.rst:72
msgid ""
"For guidance on writing good commit messages, see `How to Write a Git Commit "
"Message <https://cbea.ms/git-commit/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:74
msgid ""
"To ensure your commit message is properly formatted (wrapped at 72 "
"characters), use the included formatter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:76
msgid "Write your commit message in a text file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:77
msgid ""
"Run ``python fmt_commit_msg.py commitmsg.txt`` (this formats the file in-"
"place)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:78
msgid ""
"Paste the formatted message in your PR description, wrapped in triple "
"backticks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:80
msgid "The maintainer will use this message when squash-merging your PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:83
msgid "Implementing New Features"
msgstr "實現新功能"

#: ../../../contributing.rst:85
msgid ""
"If you are writing a new feature, please ensure you write appropriate Pytest "
"test cases and place them under ``tests/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:87
msgid ""
"If you are making a larger change, please consult first with the `Vyper "
"(Smart Contract Programming Language) Discord <https://discord."
"gg/6tw7PTM7C2>`_ ``#compiler-dev`` channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:89
msgid ""
"Although we do CI testing, please make sure that the tests pass for "
"supported Python version and ensure that it builds locally before submitting "
"a pull request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing.rst:91
msgid "Thank you for your help!"
msgstr ""
